VSFTP Configuration

Package: vsftpd

Daemon: /usr/sbin/vsftpd

Stop & Start Procedures:
		#service vsftpd stop/start/restart/status

Ports 21 (ftp control channel) All commands user send and the ftp serverâ€™s responses will go over the control connection,but any data sent back will go over the data connection.

Ports 20 (ftp-data) This port is used for all subsequent data transfers between the client and servers.

Configuration: /etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf/

Restriction: 
/etc/vsftpd/ftpusers 
/etc/vsftpd/user_list


Log: /var/log/xferlog

Configure VSFTP

Step 1: Install vsftpd package

	#rpm -ivh vsftpd*
	Or
	#yum install vsftpd

Step 2: Edit configuration files, if required

	vi /etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf/
	vi /etc/vsftpd/ftpusers 
	vi /etc/vsftpd/user_list

Step 3: Start VSFTPD service

	#service vsftpd start

FTP Commands

ftp abc.xyz.edu
<username & password>

ftp> help

ftp> ls

ftp> cd customers

ftp> lcd images

ftp> binary

ftp> hash

ftp> get testfile.txt

ftp> put testfile1.txt

ftp> mget *.txt

ftp> mput *.jpg

ftp> bye




